  "claim_short": "The proposed characterization is false. In fact, for arbitrary Tychonoff spaces \\(X\\) and \\(Y\\), every semi-embedding \\(T:C_p(X)\\to C_p(Y)\\) is already a topological embedding. Therefore the property in Problem 10 holds for every infinite compact \\(X\\), including non-scattered compacta such as \\(X=[0,1]\\).",
